				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				I agree with Tinkerbell. I am a gnomish tinkerer and cannot tell you how much plat I've blown trying to increase my skill so I can finally make rebreathers. This is a skill a gnome must learn in the field. You cannot train it up. Some of you say, &quot;Oh those greedy little gnomes! I'm going to make my own gnome tinkerer and make my rebreathers and save loads of money!&quot; Well guess what? You'll spend THOUSANDS of plat just trying to get the skill high enough to even attempt it. Besides that, you need to be at least level 16 before you can even increase your tinkering skill. <BR>
<BR>
Don't be stupid. Do yourself a favor. Buy the damned things for 5k apiece and SAVE yourself a lot of time and money. I'm happy that making rebreathers is actually useful now. Anyone can cast enduring breath / dead man floating. This quest will give our trade some real value. I just hope the sword is worth the trouble... Anyone gonna post the stats???<BR>
