				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				A note on the folks who complain about the rebreathers and thier cost.<BR>
Tinkering is the MOST expensive trade skill there is.  Jewelrycraft does not<BR>
even come close.  When you pay your 2k-5k for a high end tinkered item,<BR>
you are paying for all the time and effort it took that person to get to the<BR>
skill level that enables them to make that item.  I think 5k is a bit extreme,<BR>
but 2k is not out of line at all.<BR>
<BR>
a gnome tinkeress
